31/01/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer has reaffirmed support for Croatia's bid to join the Alliance. 
During a meeting with Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader in Brussels Monday (30 January), he pledged that NATO would assist Zagreb in achieving this goal. 
He also called for continued reforms, noting that the accession of any candidate is performance-based. 
Sanader, meanwhile, stressed that NATO membership is a top priority for his country.
In other news, leaders of Croatia's opposition Liberal Party endorsed a merger deal with the Croatian Social Liberal Party. 
Supporters hope to attract 10 per cent to 15 per cent of the vote in Croatia's next parliamentary elections. 
(Novi list - 31/01/06; NATO Web site, HINA - 30/01/06)
